NAME
trim_buf - Remove a complete message from an mgebuffer struct.
SYNOPSIS
#include <mgebuffer.h>

struct mgebuffer *trim_buf(struct mgebuffer *msg_buf);

DESCRIPTION
trim_buf() removes the message (from 0 to the value of the offset field) from
the buffer.

PARAMETERS
msg_buf - a pointer to the mgebuffer struct buffer to use.

RETURN VALUE
Return value is a pointer to the updated mgebuffer struct or NULL on error.

ERRORS
mge_errno is set as required.
On error the functions arguments are unchanged.

